ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
The softly-lit interior of the house is extravagantly furnished, in stark
contrast to its rather dull exterior. As you gaze about the room, the first
thing you notice are the frecso-covered walls vividly depicting the people and
places of Andor. Beneath your feet you feel the soft cushion of a luxurious
woven rug. Across the room, above a huge stone fireplace, hangs a simple, yet
regal, coat of arms. In front of the fireplace are several comfortable-looking
chairs. A delightful fragrance wafts in from an arch set into the wall just to
their right. A grandfather clock stands against the righthand wall, softly
ticking away the minutes. Next to the clock there is a sturdy-looking metal
door with an intricate lock. A misty window looks out on the intersection
outside. That's funny -- you didn't notice a window on the outside of the
house...
