dominated by a wonderful fireplace of brilliant red brick its character is
defined by the profusion of comfortable chairs and couches arrayed about the
floor, each facing towards a common center above the hearth. A mirror set
over the mantelpiece allows anyone in the room to see anyone else without
turning his or her head, while an archway leads out into the waterfall. Twin
doors of glass in a wooden frame lead into another chamber.
