*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 3
Although there seems to be no pattern to the arrangement, the prints have a
symmetry that seems oddly calming. To one side of the door are hung four
watercolors of wildflowers, delicately detailed in pen and ink and framed
with simple silver frames. On the other side are several charcoal sketches,
apparently by the same artist, of such creatures as unicorns and dragons,
winged horses and faeries.
*DESCRIPTION_END
