*DESCRIPTION_START
You enter what is obviously the living area of the house to find a typical
batchelor home. You see a table with an open book laying next to an empty
flagon and the remains of the last meal. Although it appears fairly clean,
closer inspection would reveal a several days layer of dust in many places.
On the west wall, next to the door, is a large painting of a forest scene,
on the east wall a row of bookshelves full of books on various subjects
from healing to warfare to foraging. To your right you see a display of
several drakin weapons. Unlike the rest of the room, everything in the
display is clean and well oiled showing recent care. To your left is a
fireplace covering most of the wall except for the door to another room.
*DESCRIPTION_END
