*DESCRIPTION_START
Canvas tarpaulins cover the floor, and plaster dust hangs in the air in this
long hallway. Long curls of wallpaper lay in the corners, testament to the
work that is proceeding, and buckets of paint are stacked against one wall.
The numberplates have been removed from each of the four doors, and the
doors are freshly sanded. At the end of the hallway, a narrow stairway leads
up to more rooms.
*DESCRIPTION_END
