*DESCRIPTION_START
The clean smell of fresh paint pervades the air, testifying to the work
being done here. The gleaming window is framed with midnight blue curtains
that contrast perfectly with the pale blue of the walls. Crated furniture
covered with a paint-spattered tarp is stacked against one wall, awaiting
completion of the renovations. A solid oak door leads back out into the hallway.
*DESCRIPTION_END

NUMBER 1581
NAME Bare Room
FIXED_LIGHT
INDOOR_FLOOR
CALL 33
ITEM 2 65 OPEN UNLOCKED VAL2=1579
*DESCRIPTION_START
The fresh white stuccoed walls brighten the room, making it seem larger and
more open. The hardwood floor is freshly sanded, and two cans of varnish
stand in the corner, ready to give it a final coat of polish. The solid
maple heartwood of the door and window frames has been sanded to reveal the
beauty of the natural grain. Against one wall, tarps cover crated furniture
that will grace the room when it is completed.
*DESCRIPTION_END

